answers.body_markdown:
Issue here is that the ManyToOne mappings are using the JPA default column n name values because you haven&#39;t defined the JoinColumn definition, so in the case of OrderItem.order, the FK column used becomes order_id_order. MapsId tells JPA that the ManyToOne mapping defines the column and the values, so that the column annotations on the ID field are not used.

This should be:

    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
    @MapsId(&quot;idOrder&quot;)
    @JoinColumn(name=&quot;id_order&quot;)
    private EshopOrder order;
 
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
    @MapsId(&quot;idProduct&quot;)
    @JoinColumn(name=&quot;id_product&quot;)
    private Product product;

